main.java.questfortheabodeth.weapons

Class Bullet

  • java.lang.Object
    • main.java.questfortheabodeth.sprites.Image
      • main.java.questfortheabodeth.weapons.Bullet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Collidable, Movable, org.jsfml.graphics.Drawable 

    public class Bullet
extends Image
implements Movable, Collidable
    Class that describes a bullet. Once fired, a bullet will travel in a straight line across the map and then disappear when it is off the screen. If the bullet hits a collidable it will disappear.

      • Bullet

        public Bullet(int x,
              int y,
              double angle,
              int damage,
              boolean hurtsPlayer,
              java.lang.String type)
        Creates a new bullet object. Bullets can differ depending on who fired them e.g. the Player or a ShootingArrows
        Parameters:
        x - (int) X coordinate of the top left of the image
        y - (int) Y coordinate of the top left of the image
        angle - (double) Angle the bullet is travelling at clockwise about the vertical
        damage - (int) Amount of damage this bullet will do
        hurtsPlayer - (boolean) Whether or not this bullet can hurt the player
        type - (String) The tye of bullet to load
